WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:01:45.563 --> 00:01:47.899 position:50% align:center
[LILIANA] "Eri Nakamura,
who had a common interest

00:01:47.982 --> 00:01:50.151 position:50% align:center
with the demons,
orchestrated the invasion

00:01:50.235 --> 00:01:52.612 position:50% align:center
of the royal capital.

00:01:52.696 --> 00:01:55.281 position:50% align:center
Using her natural
talent for necromancy,

00:01:55.365 --> 00:01:57.409 position:50% align:center
Eri employed the corpse
of the female demon

00:01:57.492 --> 00:01:59.911 position:50% align:center
that she had encountered
in the Great Orcus Labyrinth

00:01:59.994 --> 00:02:02.122 position:50% align:center
to deliver a message.

00:02:02.205 --> 00:02:03.164 position:50% align:center
That is how she managed

00:02:03.248 --> 00:02:06.126 position:50% align:center
to get in contact
with the demons.

00:02:06.209 --> 00:02:08.003 position:50% align:center
Then, in exchange
for helping the demons

00:02:08.086 --> 00:02:10.588 position:50% align:center
access the capital and
murdering both the knighthood

00:02:10.672 --> 00:02:13.383 position:50% align:center
and her classmates,
Eri bargained with the demons

00:02:13.466 --> 00:02:16.302 position:50% align:center
for her freedom, and that
of Kouki Amanogawa,

00:02:16.386 --> 00:02:18.972 position:50% align:center
one of her classmates.

00:02:19.055 --> 00:02:21.349 position:50% align:center
Because her unique magic,
Spirit Binding,

00:02:21.433 --> 00:02:23.727 position:50% align:center
only works immediately
after her target's death,

00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:26.646 position:50% align:center
and can therefore only be used
on one victim at a time,

00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:31.067 position:50% align:center
we believe she picked off
her classmates slowly.

00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:33.820 position:50% align:center
Fortunately, the invasion
was a failure,

00:02:33.903 --> 00:02:37.615 position:50% align:center
but Eri Nakamura escaped
with the demons nevertheless.

00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:40.201 position:50% align:center
We do not believe that Eri
brainwashed or murdered

00:02:40.285 --> 00:02:42.662 position:50% align:center
our king herself,
rather that it was the nun

00:02:42.746 --> 00:02:45.915 position:50% align:center
from the Divine Mountain,
the kidnapper of Aiko Hatayama,

00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:48.418 position:50% align:center
who perpetrated
these atrocities.

00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:51.504 position:50% align:center
Unfortunately, this nun
is still at large.

00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:53.798 position:50% align:center
We are seeking
more information."

00:03:02.682 --> 00:03:04.351 position:50% align:center
[LILIANA]
Out of the transferees,

00:03:04.434 --> 00:03:08.813 position:50% align:center
we've lost Daisuke Hiyama,
Reiichi Kondo.

00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:15.737 position:50% align:center
And Kaori Shirasaki.

00:03:36.508 --> 00:03:37.592 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Where's Ms. Aiko?

00:03:37.676 --> 00:03:38.843 position:50% align:center
I'm not sure.

00:03:38.927 --> 00:03:41.221 position:50% align:center
I know she was taking
a break, though.

00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:42.305 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
I see.

00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:45.308 position:50% align:center
[YUE]
Hajime. Kaori will be all right.

00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:48.478 position:50% align:center
Please go talk to Aiko.

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:50.021 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:58.571 position:50% align:center
I'm so sorry.

00:04:02.826 --> 00:04:04.411 position:50% align:center
Nagumo.

00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:11.084 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
You don't have to smile for me.

00:04:11.167 --> 00:04:12.377 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.170 position:50% align:center
You care about your students
more than anything

00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:16.881 position:50% align:center
and I killed some of them.

00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:19.175 position:50% align:center
I'm sure that's
weighing on you.

00:04:21.511 --> 00:04:22.721 position:50% align:center
To be honest,

00:04:22.804 --> 00:04:26.307 position:50% align:center
it's going to take me
a while to get over it.

00:04:26.391 --> 00:04:28.143 position:50% align:center
I could never forgive
what Hiyama did,

00:04:28.226 --> 00:04:29.936 position:50% align:center
and he didn't
deserve forgiveness.

00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:32.480 position:50% align:center
But if he were still alive,
if you hadn't killed him,

00:04:32.564 --> 00:04:35.150 position:50% align:center
at least there'd be the
possibility he could atone.

00:04:35.233 --> 00:04:37.360 position:50% align:center
And yet, at the same time,
I can understand the rage

00:04:37.444 --> 00:04:40.155 position:50% align:center
you must have felt towards him.

00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:42.615 position:50% align:center
Anyway, it's useless.

00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:45.910 position:50% align:center
I've no right to criticize you,
knowing my part in it.

00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:48.038 position:50% align:center
Ms. Aiko, you were
just helping out.

00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:49.622 position:50% align:center
Don't be so hard on yourself.

00:04:49.706 --> 00:04:51.666 position:50% align:center
At the end of the day, it was
Tio's breath that killed them.

00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:53.668 position:50% align:center
That isn't the point,
and you know it!

00:04:53.752 --> 00:04:55.211 position:50% align:center
I helped Tio with
the full knowledge

00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:56.755 position:50% align:center
that people could get killed!

00:04:56.838 --> 00:04:58.631 position:50% align:center
But I still did it,
don't you see?

00:04:58.715 --> 00:05:02.260 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] Are you saying that
you regret that choice?

00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:03.553 position:50% align:center
No.

00:05:03.636 --> 00:05:04.721 position:50% align:center
In that moment,

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:07.057 position:50% align:center
I felt justified in my choice.

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:08.892 position:50% align:center
I couldn't just sit back
and let the church

00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:11.561 position:50% align:center
continue doing
what it was doing.

00:05:11.644 --> 00:05:14.981 position:50% align:center
I wanted to help you.
I had to stop them.

00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:18.568 position:50% align:center
I knew if I didn't,
my students would suffer.

00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:23.948 position:50% align:center
So, no. I've no regrets.
It was worth it.

00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:29.871 position:50% align:center
Well, that's good to hear.

00:05:29.954 --> 00:05:31.831 position:50% align:center
So, you'll act like
my teacher again?

00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:33.708 position:50% align:center
[AIKO]
Huh?

00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:35.543 position:50% align:center
If so, if you still
think you've got

00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:38.129 position:50% align:center
what it takes to be
a role model for us,

00:05:38.213 --> 00:05:41.966 position:50% align:center
then would you indulge me just
one, very selfish request?

00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:44.719 position:50% align:center
A request? That depends.

00:05:44.803 --> 00:05:46.388 position:50% align:center
I want you to keep
feeling guilty

00:05:46.471 --> 00:05:48.181 position:50% align:center
for the harm you've perpetrated.

00:05:48.264 --> 00:05:51.851 position:50% align:center
And I want you to keep on
carrying that weight.

00:05:51.935 --> 00:05:53.603 position:50% align:center
Fighting for the right reasons,

00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:56.564 position:50% align:center
feeling the burden of violence,
always doing the right thing,

00:05:56.648 --> 00:05:58.775 position:50% align:center
and agonizing over every death.

00:05:58.858 --> 00:06:00.944 position:50% align:center
In essence, knowing who you are.

00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:03.738 position:50% align:center
Staying in touch
with your humanity.

00:06:03.822 --> 00:06:05.740 position:50% align:center
All those degrees of
empathy are lost to me

00:06:05.824 --> 00:06:08.743 position:50% align:center
at this point,
but, as my teacher,

00:06:08.827 --> 00:06:11.371 position:50% align:center
you can show me what
it means to be human.

00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.581 position:50% align:center
I'll keep my eye on you.

00:06:13.665 --> 00:06:16.126 position:50% align:center
That way, when I make it
back to Japan,

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:18.461 position:50% align:center
I can live a proper, human life.

00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:23.174 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Oh, Nagumo.

00:06:25.301 --> 00:06:27.470 position:50% align:center
That said, if one day
you find that you're in

00:06:27.554 --> 00:06:30.015 position:50% align:center
so much pain you feel like
you're about to break,

00:06:30.098 --> 00:06:33.059 position:50% align:center
and it seems like there's
nobody else you can rely on...

00:06:35.186 --> 00:06:38.690 position:50% align:center
...you can cry on my shoulder.

00:06:38.773 --> 00:06:40.358 position:50% align:center
Thanks for that.

00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:43.361 position:50% align:center
You're much nicer
than you think you are.

00:06:43.445 --> 00:06:44.571 position:50% align:center
And if I need to,

00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:47.282 position:50% align:center
I'll take you up on
that sometime, Nagumo.

00:06:47.365 --> 00:06:49.993 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Well, then. How 'bout now?

00:07:02.672 --> 00:07:03.882 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:06.343 --> 00:07:07.761 position:50% align:center
And halt!

00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:10.472 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:18.897 position:50% align:center
Seems that took it out
of you. Feeling tired?

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:22.400 position:50% align:center
Lily. No, I'm all right.

00:07:22.484 --> 00:07:24.194 position:50% align:center
You, on the other hand,
haven't slept much at all

00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:25.904 position:50% align:center
these past five days, have you?

00:07:25.987 --> 00:07:28.073 position:50% align:center
Don't worry about me,
I'm quite well.

00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:30.784 position:50% align:center
I am working hard, but
the citizens who've lost

00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:33.495 position:50% align:center
their loved ones and
livelihoods have it worse.

00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:35.789 position:50% align:center
When I feel fatigued,
I just think of them.

00:07:35.872 --> 00:07:38.917 position:50% align:center
You're one of them.
You lost your father--

00:07:41.002 --> 00:07:43.046 position:50% align:center
Please, don't feel bad.

00:07:43.129 --> 00:07:44.422 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry.

00:07:44.506 --> 00:07:47.300 position:50% align:center
How is Shizuku faring
with all this?

00:07:47.384 --> 00:07:49.969 position:50% align:center
Nothing's changed.

00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:51.554 position:50% align:center
She'll be totally normal,
and then she gets

00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:55.392 position:50% align:center
this blank stare
and just goes away.

00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.936 position:50% align:center
[LILIANA] She'll be that
way until they return.

00:07:58.019 --> 00:08:01.690 position:50% align:center
To be honest, I don't think
I can trust Nagumo.

00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:05.652 position:50% align:center
And sometimes I wish Shizuku
would never talk to him again.

00:08:12.659 --> 00:08:13.868 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:15.537 --> 00:08:17.872 position:50% align:center
Look! Kouki, look! Up there!

00:08:17.956 --> 00:08:20.208 position:50% align:center
Something's descending
from way up in the sky!

00:08:20.291 --> 00:08:22.502 position:50% align:center
What? What are you
talking about?

00:08:24.087 --> 00:08:28.466 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Heads up, everyone!
Something's coming from above!

00:08:33.680 --> 00:08:38.101 position:50% align:center
[KNIGHTS coughing]

00:08:40.729 --> 00:08:44.190 position:50% align:center
[SHEA coughing]

00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.026 position:50% align:center
It's Nagumo!

00:08:46.109 --> 00:08:48.153 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey, Yaegashi.

00:08:48.236 --> 00:08:50.530 position:50% align:center
Glad to see that you're alive.

00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:53.283 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:55.910 position:50% align:center
Where is she? Kaori.

00:08:55.994 --> 00:08:57.912 position:50% align:center
Why isn't she here, Nagumo?

00:08:57.996 --> 00:09:00.665 position:50% align:center
Uh, she'll be here soon.

00:09:00.749 --> 00:09:02.709 position:50% align:center
But, like, brace yourself,
because she looks

00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:05.086 position:50% align:center
a little different than
you remember her.

00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:08.298 position:50% align:center
Um. And look, it's not my fault,
so don't blame me, okay?

00:09:08.381 --> 00:09:12.093 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry, what?
She... what, now?

00:09:12.177 --> 00:09:14.054 position:50% align:center
Okay, you're totally
freaking me out.

00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:15.513 position:50% align:center
What happened?

00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:17.432 position:50% align:center
Tell me what you did
to Kaori, you jerk!

00:09:17.515 --> 00:09:20.018 position:50% align:center
[KAORI yelling]

00:09:20.101 --> 00:09:22.562 position:50% align:center
Hajime!

00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:23.480 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:24.773 position:50% align:center
Wait, that voice--?

00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:28.860 position:50% align:center
Catch me, please!

00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:30.320 position:50% align:center
U-Uh--

00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:52.050 position:50% align:center
[KAORI whines]

00:09:52.133 --> 00:09:54.135 position:50% align:center
What is this? Wh-Who are you?

00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:55.679 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU]
Kouki, wait!

00:09:55.762 --> 00:09:57.389 position:50% align:center
[KOUKI]
What? Why?

00:10:03.019 --> 00:10:09.067 position:50% align:center
Kaori, is--? It's you, isn't it?

00:10:09.150 --> 00:10:11.361 position:50% align:center
[LILIANA, KOUKI gasp]

00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:13.530 position:50% align:center
[KAORI]
Yep! Good eye!

00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:16.199 position:50% align:center
Shizuku, it's me,
your best friend, Kaori.

00:10:16.282 --> 00:10:18.201 position:50% align:center
I might look a little
different than before,

00:10:18.284 --> 00:10:20.286 position:50% align:center
but I'm alive and well!

00:10:27.419 --> 00:10:28.920 position:50% align:center
Kaori.

00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:32.757 position:50% align:center
Kaori!

00:10:32.841 --> 00:10:36.720 position:50% align:center
[crying]

00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:41.683 position:50% align:center
I'm so sorry if I worried
you, but I'm okay.

00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:43.435 position:50% align:center
Everything's all right now.

00:10:43.518 --> 00:10:47.397 position:50% align:center
I'm so glad!
I was so afraid!

00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50% align:center
[SHIZUKU]
All right, then.

00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:58.658 position:50% align:center
What the heck is going on here?

00:10:58.742 --> 00:11:00.368 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Well, to put it simply.

00:11:00.452 --> 00:11:02.871 position:50% align:center
We used magic to
protect Kaori's soul,

00:11:02.954 --> 00:11:04.289 position:50% align:center
then we repaired Noint's body

00:11:04.372 --> 00:11:07.709 position:50% align:center
and transplanted
Kaori's soul into it.

00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:10.503 position:50% align:center
Interesting. I don't get it.

00:11:10.587 --> 00:11:13.882 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Well, um.
Here's the deal.

00:11:13.965 --> 00:11:16.259 position:50% align:center
We learned before that
the magic we normally use

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:18.678 position:50% align:center
is just an inferior copy
of the magic from the era

00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:21.473 position:50% align:center
called the God's Age, right?
You with me so far?

00:11:21.556 --> 00:11:23.350 position:50% align:center
Yes, the magic they mention

00:11:23.433 --> 00:11:25.894 position:50% align:center
in this world's
creation mythology.

00:11:25.977 --> 00:11:27.812 position:50% align:center
It works on a fundamental level,

00:11:27.896 --> 00:11:31.483 position:50% align:center
unlike the elemental magic
we use in this age.

00:11:31.566 --> 00:11:32.984 position:50% align:center
Hold on.

00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:34.694 position:50% align:center
Are you saying what
I think you are?

00:11:34.778 --> 00:11:37.989 position:50% align:center
That Nagumo can use God's Age
magic to manipulate souls?

00:11:38.073 --> 00:11:39.240 position:50% align:center
Is that right?

00:11:39.324 --> 00:11:40.367 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Mm-hm.

00:11:40.450 --> 00:11:41.618 position:50% align:center
Now I get it.

00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:44.037 position:50% align:center
You used that to protect
Kaori's soul from death

00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:45.997 position:50% align:center
and transfer it to another body.

00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:49.250 position:50% align:center
Yes! I knew you'd
catch on, Shizuku.

00:11:49.334 --> 00:11:52.045 position:50% align:center
But, like, why'd you
pick that body?

00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:54.214 position:50% align:center
Was her old body
really that far gone?

00:11:54.297 --> 00:11:56.966 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] Nah, we were able to
restore Kaori's original one,

00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.010 position:50% align:center
and we could have put
her soul back in it.

00:11:59.094 --> 00:12:00.512 position:50% align:center
Then why didn't you?

00:12:00.595 --> 00:12:02.138 position:50% align:center
[KAORI]
Because I asked them not to.

00:12:02.222 --> 00:12:03.348 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:12:03.431 --> 00:12:07.310 position:50% align:center
It was my choice and
I wanted to be stronger.

00:12:08.603 --> 00:12:11.147 position:50% align:center
You know Kaori. Gets an
idea and won't shut up.

00:12:11.231 --> 00:12:13.441 position:50% align:center
As far as her original form,

00:12:13.525 --> 00:12:16.444 position:50% align:center
we stored it in a suspended
state using magic.

00:12:16.528 --> 00:12:20.323 position:50% align:center
She's free to go back
to it whenever she wants.

00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:21.741 position:50% align:center
That all makes sense.

00:12:21.825 --> 00:12:24.244 position:50% align:center
Huh. Kaori always did get
the most hairbrained ideas

00:12:24.327 --> 00:12:26.204 position:50% align:center
in that head of hers,
but I gotta say,

00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:27.789 position:50% align:center
this one takes the cake.

00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:30.917 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Sorry again
for worrying you.

00:12:31.001 --> 00:12:33.628 position:50% align:center
Don't be. You're still
alive, aren't you?

00:12:33.712 --> 00:12:35.255 position:50% align:center
It's all good.

00:12:38.258 --> 00:12:42.429 position:50% align:center
So, Nagumo, Yue, Shea,
Tio, I thank you.

00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:44.180 position:50% align:center
I am eternally grateful to you.

00:12:44.264 --> 00:12:46.808 position:50% align:center
You saved my best friend.

00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:48.977 position:50% align:center
I can never repay this debt.

00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:52.147 position:50% align:center
If there is anything I can do,
you just have to ask.

00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:55.400 position:50% align:center
I'll do my best to make good.

00:12:55.483 --> 00:12:57.902 position:50% align:center
You're as honorable
as ever, aren't ya?

00:12:57.986 --> 00:13:00.280 position:50% align:center
Don't make a big deal
out of it, 'kay?

00:13:00.363 --> 00:13:01.698 position:50% align:center
We didn't do anything crazy.

00:13:01.781 --> 00:13:04.617 position:50% align:center
We just saved our
friend, that's all.

00:13:04.701 --> 00:13:06.703 position:50% align:center
You say that,
but you did console me

00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:08.204 position:50% align:center
when things went south,

00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:11.833 position:50% align:center
and you used some of your
precious medicine on our Kouki.

00:13:13.668 --> 00:13:15.295 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] Meh, if you'd
had a total breakdown,

00:13:15.378 --> 00:13:17.714 position:50% align:center
